sentence: Irene "Rena" Vlahopoulou (Greek: Ειρήνη (Ρένα) Βλαχοπούλου; 28 July 1917– 29 July 2004) was a Greek actress and singer.
She starred in theatre, musical, and Greek cinema productions, including The Gambler and The Countess of Corfu.
Vlahopoulou was born on the island of Corfu, the fifth of nine children.
When she turned ten, she began singing at a local bakery; she was a talented dancer and actress and a qualified mezzo-soprano.
In 1939, Vlahopoulou and AEK footballer Kostas Vasileiou eloped to Athens and were married.
